      <memberdef kind="variable" id="structads1299__continuous__config__t_1a93db9c124ee88b669d56081530171ea2" prot="public" static="no" mutable="no">
        <type>uint32_t</type>
        <definition>uint32_t ads1299_continuous_config_t::ring_buffer_chunks</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>ring_buffer_chunks</name>
        <qualifiedname>ads1299_continuous_config_t::ring_buffer_chunks</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Ring buffer depth in number of chunk slots. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>0 = ADS1299_RING_BUF_SLOTS (default).</para>
<para>Must be a power of 2. Rounded up internally if not.</para>
<para>Total memory allocated: ring_buffer_chunks * chunk_samples * sizeof(ads1299_sample_t)</para>
<para>At 250 SPS, 100 ms chunks, 8 slots: 8 * 25 * 44 = 8,800 bytes</para>
<para>At 16 kSPS, 10 ms chunks, 8 slots: 8 * 160 * 44 = 56,320 bytes</para>
<para>At 16 kSPS, 100 ms chunks, 8 slots: 8 * 1600 * 44 = 563,200 bytes ← EXCEEDS ESP32 SRAM; reduce chunk_duration_ms </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
